cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is about a self-supervised framework for robots to learn to navigate based on vision, which is a problem in robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV). The framework uses a deep network architecture that is incrementally built as new data becomes available, which involves machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.RO and cs.CV, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.NE.
